Selenium class 1:
What is software testing :
identify correctness and quality of application

How many way can we test:
-manual
-automation

When do we go for automation
-after manual testing has passed
-when environment is stable
-analyze our test suite and choose our automation tools

What other tools do we know for automation?
-selenium, UFT/QTP, Cucumber, Test NG, Katalon Studio

Levels of Testing?
-Unit test
-Acceptance testing
-System testing
-Integration testing

types of testing?
-functional testing
-non functional testing
   performance testing
   security testing

What is Selenium?
-is a set of tools which help us automate web applications. It's mainly used to
perform functional testing


Selenium components:
-selenium IDE -->
-selenium Grid-->
-selenium WebDriver-->
-selenium RC

What is Selenium WebDriver ?
Open source automation tool which allows us to perform actions on a web application
WebDriver is an interface


Advantages of Selenium WebDriver:
-open source
-works with different programing languages -->Java, ruby, C#, Javascript, python
-works with multiple browsers and suports cros browser testing
-OS independent -> ios, linux, windows

Disadvantages of selenium WebDriver:
-No tecnical support
-Cannot automate desktop applications
-no built in reports
-cannot test captchas, images,videos
-takes more time to create test cases

get() vs navigate()
-navigate can move back, foward and refresh
-get() will wait for page to fully load whereas navigate () will not
-get() will not keep the history of the browser whereas navigate () will

close() vs quite()
-close () will close the current tab
-quite() will quite the whole browser

fullscreen() vs maximize()
-maximize () will maximize the browser and you will still be able to see url, tabs, bookmarks
and fullscreen () will maximize the whole web application


